                  <width quantity="420"/><height quantity="30"/></dimensions><dimensions type="written" unit="mm"/></extent><collation><desc xml:id="CoverFront">the <emph rend="bold">front cover</emph>. 418 x 29 mm.</desc><desc xml:id="U1">1 + 1 + 1 + 108 + 2 folios = <title xml:lang="ta">Veṅkaikkōvai</title>.</desc><desc xml:id="U1a">1 folio = <title xml:lang="ta">Veṅkaikkōvai</title>: <emph rend="bold">Title Page 1 (additional)</emph>. The leaf appears to be original and was inscribed later with the title. No foliation. Verso blank. 414 x 30 mm.</desc><desc xml:id="U1b">1 folio = <title xml:lang="ta">Veṅkaikkōvai</title>: <emph rend="bold">Title Page 2 (additional)</emph>. The leaf appears to be original and was inscribed later with the title. No foliation. Verso blank. 413 x 30 mm.</desc><desc xml:id="U1c">1 folio = <title xml:lang="ta">Veṅkaikkōvai</title>: <emph rend="bold">Invocation</emph>. The leaf appears to be original and was inscribed later with the invocation. No foliation. Verso blank. 412 x 30 mm.</desc><desc xml:id="U1d">108 folios = <title xml:lang="ta">Veṅkaikkōvai</title>: <emph rend="bold">Text</emph>. Tamil foliation 1-33.1, 33.2, 35-107. f33.2 in fact foliated "33-34" by a later hand, that is, original foliation missing, by oversight of the original copyist, has been supplied by a later hand. f33.2v left blank, also by oversight of the original copyist. Alternatively: missing stanzas added by the original copyist, inserting a folio without foliating it. 415 x 30 mm.</desc><desc xml:id="U1e">2 folios = <emph rend="bold">guard leaves</emph>. Blank recto verso, except for a few unblackened letters on the left side of <locus facs="226">f[1]r</locus>. 413 x 30 mm. </desc><desc xml:id="CoverBack">the <emph rend="bold">back cover</emph>.</desc></collation><condition>Excellent state of preservation.</condition></supportDesc>
